    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-05-13T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-05-13T12:00:00-05:00" n="1166"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1166">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">641.74/5–1353: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1166<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            type="from">Caffery</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1166fn1">Repeated to Amman priority for the Secretary of
                        State as telegram 73 and to London as telegram 780.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-05-13T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 13, 1953—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2428. At Secretary’s direction I told British Ambassador and General <persName
                        corresp="#p_RGS1">Robertson</persName> this evening that as result of
                    conversations with Egyptian leaders he has come to following conclusions:</p>
                <pb facs="0371" n="2073" xml:id="pg_2073"/>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>We should continue publicly to stand with British;</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>“Case A” is unobtainable and therefore he believes a move should be made
                        in direction of “Case B”;<note n="2" xml:id="d1166fn2">Regarding “Cases A
                            and B,” see <ref target="#d1061">Document 1061</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Egyptians did not raise question of $11 million interim arms purchase and
                        US does not plan to give arms list to Egyptians at this time;</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>It is Secretary’s intention to discuss whole situation with President and
                            <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> upon his return to Washington and
                        thereafter get in touch with London and endeavor to agree on new
                        approach;</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NGM1">Naguib</persName> indicated he will endeavor in
                        meantime to avoid all violent activities on part of Egyptians;</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_MEDO1">MEDO</gloss> is completely unacceptable to
                            Egyptians.<note n="3" xml:id="d1166fn3">In telegram 2434 from Cairo, May
                            14, not printed, Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                                >Caffery</persName> reported that Stevenson and <persName
                                corresp="#p_RGS1">Robertson</persName> had little to say in reply to
                            the contents of this telegram. He said they did not seem surprised, and
                            he believed that their opinions regarding Case A and <gloss
                                target="#t_MEDO1">MEDO</gloss> approximated those held by American
                            officials. (641.74/5–1453)</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
